00:44:43.040 --> 00:44:46.435
a quantitative understanding of
our species collective memory

00:44:46.435 --> 00:44:49.450
and of the role of languages
and communication technologies

00:44:49.450 --> 00:44:52.262
in the production and diffusion
of cultural information.

00:45:19.313 --> 00:45:22.980
Immersion is a design experiment
that inverts a person's email

00:45:22.980 --> 00:45:26.159
inbox by centering it on
people, rather than messages.

00:45:30.542 --> 00:45:32.250
Immersion reveals the
web of interactions

00:45:32.250 --> 00:45:34.570
that people create over
long periods of time,

00:45:34.570 --> 00:45:38.110
helping uncover the information
embodied in metadata,

00:45:38.110 --> 00:45:40.934
but also facilitating the
study of the networks that

00:45:40.934 --> 00:45:41.725
form organizations.

00:45:58.518 --> 00:46:00.750
Place Pulse and
StreetScore are efforts

00:46:00.750 --> 00:46:03.231
to create high resolution
maps of people's perceptions

00:46:03.231 --> 00:46:04.180
of urban environments.

00:46:07.000 --> 00:46:09.597
These maps have been shown to
correlate with crime levels.

00:46:09.597 --> 00:46:11.930
But also, we're now using
them to create computer vision

00:46:11.930 --> 00:46:14.680
tools that help us
study urban change.

00:46:29.901 --> 00:46:31.580
Finally, Dive is an
effort to automate

00:46:31.580 --> 00:46:35.300
the creation of simple
data visualization engines.

00:46:35.300 --> 00:46:37.330
Unlike traditional
visualization tools

00:46:37.330 --> 00:46:39.940
that ask users to decide
which visualizations

00:46:39.940 --> 00:46:42.570
they want to make a priori,
Dive has the ability

00:46:42.570 --> 00:46:45.483
to recommend visualizations
to users, facilitating

00:46:45.483 --> 00:46:49.570
the exploration of their data.

00:46:49.570 --> 00:46:51.775
Together, these
technologies are helping

00:46:51.775 --> 00:46:55.450
us understand the evolution
of global economies,

00:46:55.450 --> 00:46:57.900
regional economies,
cultural production, cities,

00:46:57.900 --> 00:46:59.370
and organizations.

00:46:59.370 --> 00:47:01.820
But unlike traditional
research methods,

00:47:01.820 --> 00:47:03.739
these tools help
us include millions

00:47:03.739 --> 00:47:05.822
of people in the exploration
of the knowledge that

00:47:05.822 --> 00:47:06.960
is hidden in our data.

